{"lemma":"رِيشٌ","slug":"رِيشٌ","root":"ر.#.ش","root_slug":"ر-_-ش","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-_-ش","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رِيش","root":"ريش","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n17248"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B4%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"feathers, quills","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"feathering, plumage","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clothes, attire, exterior","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bristles","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ribs","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to clothe in feathers"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grow feathers"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"The 20th letter of the Hebrew alphabet and other Semitic abjads. (ר)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nClassical Syriac ܪܝܫܐ (rēšā)bor.\nArabic ريش\nBorrowed from Classical Syriac ܪܝܫܐ (rēšā, “tip, extremity”). Doublet of رَأْس (raʔs). Unrelated to رِمْش (rimš, “eyelash”).\n\nEtymology tree\nClassical Syriac ܪܝܫܐ (rēšā)bor.\nArabic رِيش (rīš)denom.\nArabic ريش\nDenominal verb from رِيش (rīš).\n\nBorrowed from Hebrew רֵישׁ (rêš)"},"ipa":["/riːʃ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n17248","headword_ar":"رِيشٌ","root":"ry$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Feathers; plumage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain appertenance of birds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constituting their clothing and ornament;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA$N","text_ar":"رَاشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Kt, K:) n. un. of the former with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroyaA$N","text_ar":"اَرْيَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyaA$N","text_ar":"رِيَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IJ, K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (B,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clothing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, B:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent, clothing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyaA$N","text_ar":"رِيَاشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"both signify what appears of clothing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kt:) the former occurs in the Kur vii. 25, accord. to one reading; (S;) and ↓ the latter accord. to another reading: (TA:) and hence also, the former signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ornament;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beauty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA: *) or ↓ both signify (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plenty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundance of the produce of the earth and of the goods"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conveniences and comforts of life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or the former signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosperity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓ the latter, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness of state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a goodly state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or the former signifies, (K,) and ↓ the latter also, (TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plenty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundance of the produce of the earth and of the goods"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conveniences and comforts of life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means of subsistence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property which one has acquired for himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avaAv","text_ar":"اَثَاث"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"household-goods,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furniture and utensils,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (TA:) the Benoo-Kiláb say that ↓ the latter word means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"household-goods of whatever kind, consisting of clothes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuffing for mattresses or the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outer garments:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes it means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clothes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"exclusively of other articles or kinds of property. (ISk, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laHasanu Alr~iy$i","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَحَسَنُ الرِّيشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is goodly in clothing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Respecting the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTaAhu miAy^ipF biriy$ihaA","text_ar":"اَعْطَاهُ مِايِةً بِرِيشِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is said, (S, A, * K,) by AO, (S,) that kings, when they gave a gift, put upon the humps of the camels [that bore it] ostrich-feathers, (S, K,) or [other] feathers, (A, TA,) in order that it might be known to be the king's gift; (S, A, K;) and the meaning is, accord. to As, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave him a hundred camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with their saddles"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and their coverings:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with their coverings and their cloths beneath the saddles."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","Kt","B","ISk","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}